{{Year in Albania|1999}} The following lists events that happened during '''[[1999]] in [[Albania|Republic of Albania]]'''.
== Incumbents == * [[President of Albania|President]]: [[Rexhep Meidani]] * [[Prime Minister of Albania|Prime Minister]]: [[Pandeli Majko]] (until 29 October), [[Ilir Meta]] (starting from 29 October)
== Events ==
=== March === * 24 March - [[NATO bombing of Yugoslavia|Nato air strikes]] against Yugoslav military targets. In [[Kosovo]] thousands flee attacks by Serb forces. Mass refugee exodus into Albania.<ref name="bbc">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/country_profiles/1004984.stm Albania timeline] BBC, A chronology of key events: 1999, news.bbc.co.uk</ref>
=== October === * [[Pandeli Majko|Majko]] resigns as prime minister in October 1999, after losing [[Socialist Party of Albania|Socialist Party]] leadership vote. 30-year-old Ilir Meta becomes Europe's youngest prime minister.<ref name="bbc"/>
