Several [[heritage trail]]s have been designed in [[Hong Kong]]:
Trails designed by the [[Antiquities and Monuments Office]] of the [[Leisure and Cultural Services Department]]: * [[Ping Shan Heritage Trail]], in [[Yuen Long District]], opened on 12 December 1993 * [[Lung Yeuk Tau Heritage Trail]] * [[Central and Western Heritage Trail]]
Other trails include: * [[Dr Sun Yat-sen Historical Trail]], in [[Central and Western]] District. * Hong Kong Boulder Trackways * [[St Stephen's College (Hong Kong)#Heritage Trail|St Stephen's College Heritage Trail]]<ref>[http://www.ssc.edu.hk/ssctrail/eng/index.html St Stephen's College Heritage Trail]</ref> * [[Tai Tam Waterworks Heritage Trail]]<ref>[http://www.wsd.gov.hk/filemanager/en/share/monuments/tai_tam.pdf Tai Tam Waterworks Heritage Trail flyer] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809040706/http://www.wsd.gov.hk/filemanager/en/share/monuments/tai_tam.pdf |date=2014-08-09 }}</ref> * [[Wan Chai Heritage Trail]], launched on 27 September 2009
Military history trails * [[Pinewood Battery]] Heritage Trail, within the [[Lung Fu Shan Country Park]]<ref>[http://www.afcd.gov.hk/english/country/cou_wha/cou_wha_heriatage.html Pinewood Battery Heritage Trail]</ref> * Shing Mun War Relics Trail * [[Wong Nai Chung Gap]] Trail, opened in 2006<ref>[http://www.hkoutdoors.com/hk-island/wong-nai-chung-gap-trail.html Wong Nai Chung Gap Trail, HK Island]</ref>
