{{Infobox port | name = Muuga Harbour | image = Muuga.jpg | imagesize = 200 px | caption = Aerial view of the Muuga Harbour | country = [[Estonia]] | location = [[Viimsi Parish|Viimsi]] and [[Jõelähtme Parish|Jõelähtme]] parishes and [[Maardu]] | coordinates = {{coord|59|29|30|N|24|57|30|E|dim:3000_region:EE|display=inline,title}} | opened = {{Start date|1986}} | operated = [[Port of Tallinn]] | owner = | type = cargo port | sizewater = {{convert|7.52|km2|sqmi}} | sizeland = {{convert|5.242|km2|sqmi}} | size = | berths = 29 | wharfs = | piers = | employees = | leadershiptitle = | leader = | blankdetailstitle1 = | blankdetails1 = | blankdetailstitle2 = | blankdetails2 = | blankdetailstitle3 = | blankdetails3 = | arrivals = | cargotonnage = | containervolume = 251,738 [[Twenty-foot equivalent unit|TEU's]] (2013) <ref>{{cite news |title=Container turnover of Transiidikeskus grew by 12% in 2013 |url=http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/good_for_business/?doc=86364 |work= The Baltic Course | date = 16 January 2014 | accessdate=9 July 2014}}</ref> | cargovalue = | passengertraffic = | revenue = | profit = | blankstatstitle1 = | blankstats1 = | blankstatstitle2 = | blankstats2 = | blankstatstitle3 = | blankstats3 = | website = {{URL|http://www.portoftallinn.com/muuga-harbour}} }}
'''Muuga Harbour''' ({{lang-et|Muuga sadam}}) is the largest [[cargo ship|cargo]] [[port]] in [[Estonia]], located on the southern coast of the [[Gulf of Finland]], {{convert|13|km}} northeast of the capital [[Tallinn]], in [[Maardu]]. The harbour is administrated by [[Port of Tallinn]], the biggest port authority in Estonia. Muuga Harbour is one of the few ice-free ports in northernmost Europe and among the deepest —up to {{convert|18|m}} — and most modern ports in the Baltic Sea region. The cargo volume handled accounts for around 80% of the total cargo volume of Port of Tallinn and approximately 90% of the transit cargo volume passing through Estonia. Nearly 3/4 of cargo loaded in Muuga Harbour includes crude oil and oil products, but the harbour also serves dry bulk (mostly fertilizers, grain and coal) and other types of cargo.
The usual annual cargo traffic in the seaport is about 20–30 million tons.
The harbour covers an area of {{convert|5.24|km2}} on land and {{convert|7.5|km2}} of water. Besides Maardu, the seaport also occupies land in the villages of [[Muuga, Viimsi Parish|Muuga]] and [[Uusküla, Harju County|Uusküla]].
There are 29 quays with a total length of {{convert|6.4|km|mi|abbr=on}}. The maximum depth is {{convert|18.0|m|ft|abbr=on}}. The largest tonnage of ship that can be accommodated is {{convert|300|by|48|m|ft}}.
There are 6 liquid bulk terminals, container, grain, coal, steel and a dry bulk terminals located in the port.
<gallery> Muuga Grain Terminal 12 05 2005.jpg|Grain terminal Port of Muuga Headquarters May 2005.jpg|The headquarters Solidarnosc Stern Muuga 30 July 2005.jpg|First ship at the Muuga Coal Terminal </gallery>
