{{Expand Italian|Diocesi di Sumbe|date=February 2011}} The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Sumbe''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Sumbensis}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Sumbe]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Luanda|Luanda]] in [[Angola]].
==History== * August 10, 1975: Established as Diocese of Ngunza from the [[Metropolitan Archdiocese of Luanda]] * February 3, 1977: Renamed as Diocese of Novo Redondo * October 22, 2006: Renamed as Diocese of Sumbe
==Special churches== The Cathedral of the diocese is Sé Catedral de Nossa Senhora da Conceição (Cathedral Church of the Conception of Our Lady) in Sumbe.
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Novo Redondo (Roman rite) ** Bishop Benedito Roberto, [[C.S.Sp.]] (1995.12.15 – 2012.05.19) ** Archbishop [[Zacarias Kamwenho]] (1977.02.03 – 1995.03.03) * Bishops of Ngunza (Roman rite) ** Archbishop Zacarias Kamwenho (1975.08.10 – 1977.02.03)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in Angola]]
==Sources== * [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/nred0.htm GCatholic.org]
